
# SecureMonitor 🚀

![SafeTxt](/img/project.png)

## 🚀 Introduction

Welcome to SecureMonitor – your ultimate solution for real-time system monitoring and security. With SecureMonitor, gain unparalleled insights into your system’s health and performance, all through a sleek and modern web interface.

## 🌟 Features

- **📊 Real-Time Monitoring:** Instantly view crucial system metrics, including CPU, memory, and disk usage.
- **🌐 Network Insights:** Track your network activity with detailed statistics on bytes sent and received, and keep an eye on incoming connections.
- **📈 Performance Metrics:** Detailed stats on CPU, memory, and disk performance to ensure your system runs smoothly.
- **🖥️ System Information:** Get comprehensive details about your operating system, hostname, architecture, and kernel version.
- **💾 Disk Partitions:** See detailed information about disk partitions, including device, mountpoint, and usage.
- **🔋 Battery Status:** Monitor battery percentage, charging status, and remaining time with precision.
- **🔍 Process Monitoring:** Keep tabs on active processes and their CPU and memory usage.
- **🎨 Modern Interface:** Enjoy a responsive, stylish web interface with auto-updates every 5 seconds.

## 🚀 Quick Start

### 1. **Clone the Repository:**

```bash
$ git clone https://github.com/yourusername/SecureMonitor.git
$ cd SecureMonitor
```
### 2. **Install Dependencies:**

Create a virtual environment and install required packages:

```bash
$ python -m venv venv
$ source venv/bin/activate
$ pip install -r requirements.txt
```
### 3. **Run the Application:**

Start the Flask server to view the dashboard:

```bash
 $ python app.py
```
Navigate to http://localhost:5001 in your web browser to access the dashboard.

## 🖥️ Usage

- Open your browser and go to http://localhost:5001.
- Explore the dynamic dashboard displaying real-time data and insights.
- Click on sections to expand and view detailed information.

